Stop fighting, playing dirty tricks and campaign maturely, President Uhuru Kenyatta has told Murang&rsquo;a leaders. He also said on Tuesday he does not play favourites and endorses no one. There have been scuffles between Governor Mwangi Wairia and his arch-rival Kigumo MP Jamleck Kamau and their supporters.Uhuru spoke on Tuesday after the county abruptly removed 110 tonnes of manure it had dumped on venues to block Kamau&rsquo;s governor bid on Saturday. It claimed the manure was for landscaping. The two camps have nearly thrown punches at events. Two weeks ago four men were charged with incitement. choose good leadersThe President toured the county to launch the Murang&rsquo;a-Mukuyu Gwa Thamaki road, medical equipment at Murang&rsquo;a General Hospital and the Kangema-Gacharage road.Uhuru said he has no preferred leaders or candidates and will work with whoever is elected. He urged residents to dismiss leaders invoking his name to seek support, saying he will endorse no one.&ldquo;Some will tell you I sent you greetings through them so you can support them. I want to make it very clear that nobody should tell you I have endorsed them,&rdquo; Uhuru said.&ldquo;The people of Murang&rsquo;a are able to establish a good leader and decide who to elect.&rdquo; Addressing residents of Murang&rsquo;a town, he said there is no need for leaders to engage in physical fights and insults, when they should just market their development agenda.Uhuru urged youth to stop letting leaders use them to cause violence. &ldquo;When they address you, just listen and make your independent decision.Don&rsquo;t allow them to use you to cause violence,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;Jubilee leaders do not engage in fistfights, violence or insults. We conduct mature politics.&rdquo;